    <bug_when>2016-07-30 03:57:05 -0400</bug_when>
    <thetext>Description of problem:

When gnome3 and plasma-workspace are both installed klipper is running when chosing a gnome session on login.

This is caused by /etc/xdg/autostart/org.kde.klipper.desktop containing:

&quot;NotShowIn=KDE;&quot;

Rather then, as one would expect:

&quot;OnlyShowIn=KDE;&quot;

If this is intentional, e.g. because KDE no longer uses klipper itself, but people may still want it under another desktop, then klipper should be put in a sub-package and not installed by default.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
